The paper discusses the development of a virtual reality system for training and testing AI agents in task-oriented learning, which involves planning and reinforcement learning. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The system also involves photo-realistic rendering and object manipulation, which relates to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions learning from demonstration, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the system allows for human participation, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
